I took this class where we just read the bible as a book sophomore year and it was absolutely fascinating to me and every story was so visual. It was surprising that all of these really famous stories about Adam& eve and Noah and Jonah& the whale (it was actually a "big fish") were barely more than a few paragraphs or pages but had inspired so much art/visual culture. I had no idea the stories took up so little space. I made the armor because I found this passage in Ephesians called "the armor of god" and it talked about the breastplate of righteousness and all this stuff and I had wanted to maybe make clothing inspired by different women in the stories, mostly those without names, and I just realized that I needed to make this armor for these unnamed women
